    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.61311/-</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">2 September, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: This action on the part of Lord
                    Reading is certainly very courteous and very right and I appreciate it.<note
                        n="4" xml:id="d106fn1">See <ref target="#pg_142">p. 142</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am, however, of the same judgment as Mr. Hoover. There can be no just objection
                    on our part to any such action as the British Government has in mind with regard
                    to the price of their own domestic wheat.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
